,Not Recommended,323720,27641516,"Posted: 26 November, 2016",all,work4dvd,"Although billed as a ""3D psychological horror adventure and homage to the Resident Evil and Silent Hill games,"" the game is more akin to Myst and their various clones. The game is played from a first-person perspective, but the movement is constricted to clicking directional arrows; i.e., you ""move"" through static screens and click on various objects to pick them up or interact with them. Essentially, it is a first-person point and click adventure.That being said, it is a disappointing point and click adventure. The story is paper thin and offers few shocks and surprises. Although there is an ominous feel throughout and the music is appropriately creepy, the ""horror"" element simply falls flat; it simply isn't scary. Due to the very nature of Myst-like games, you'll often be confused directionally, especially since there's little variety in the environments. The puzzles are rather simplistic, requiring very little thought to complete once you have the requisite items. The lack of voice acting throughout is sorely missed; despite the fact that there are three other characters besides yourself, inexplicably, the only voiceover is for a short story and several newspaper clippings.I want to call attention to the English text dialogue and descriptions, which suffer from poor translation, likely due to the developers being Swedish. Since the story is important in a game such as this, the awkward sentences and word choices drag the game down significantly. (I don't know why so many developers don't enlist native English speakers to fine tune their game; it would make a huge difference.)For achievement hunters, I achieved 100% in 4.6 hours. The majority of extra time was backtracking to find coins and, for one achievement, hidden text revealed by the flash of a Polaroid camera. If you're not interested in 100% completion, the game could be blazed through in 2-3 hours.TL;DR: In a word: disappointing. It's certainly not worth the $9.99 asking price, but if you see it on sale for a dollar or in a bundle and you can overlook its flaws, it can be a mildly entertaining time waster."
