76561198124078924,Recommended,323720,14508965,"Posted: 16 February, 2015",all,Stratches,"**Half-baked horror adventure for starving fans only.**≈ 3-hour point-and-click adventure offers moody music, jump scares, and some haunting imagery. The story is paper-thin, and the reason for your character's involvement was plucked out of a hat. The puzzles are unrelated to the game's story or tone. The interface is clunky; reading a posted note requires 5 clicks and a trip to your inventory. Be ready for senseless, nagging design choices throughout. Why are newspaper clippings read by voice actors while real-time dialogue is text only? A pleasant evening for forgiving gamers."
