,Not Recommended,323720,17953667,"Posted: 9 September, 2015",all,rogermorse@tablet,"TL:DR see last 4 linesThis is a very slow and disorienting point and click adventure. For a 2015 game, the artwork could have been better and more detailed. It looks like a game from 1995, we don't need that today.The puzzles are ok but most of the time you will have to roam around until a scripted event triggers, and you can't know such thing is going to randomly (actually scripted) happen, like doors unlocking themselves after a cutscene for no reason or new items popping up only because you go to a room already visited in the past and the thing comes out of nowhere. There is no logic in that and is not a good way to make the progressing in the game harder.The atmosphere is cool but once you get a grasp of the story, you notice how empty and obvious it is.Can't believe it's a 10 euros game. I think I bought it for 1 euro or so, and I still almost regret it.There are much better or more entertaining point and click puzzle games and adventure games out there, I see no reason to recommend this one, even because it is highly overpriced (low budget game, cheap soundtrack, no voice acting almost at all). If there were a neutral rating I may agree with choosing one, but this time I will go with a thumbs down, because surely I doubt this would deserve a thumbs up."
