,Not Recommended,323720,15458102,"Posted: 19 April, 2015",all,ros,"Decay - The Mare has very little substance to it.The game style is a point- and-click puzzle horror adventure. Your character is a psychiatric patient who thinks he's woken up during the night  but then finds he is in a medicine induced nightmare that he can't seem to escape. The gameplay consists of single clicks to move around, open doors, pick up objects and solve puzzles.The people who will like this game are those who really like sudden scares. The game is full of doors slamming shut in your face, shadowy figures running on the periphery of your vision, objects being thrown at you by invisible forces... that sort of thing. If you're happy to turn the lights down, walk around an old creepy building and have things go BOO! at you, then buy the game.If is is important to you that your games have interesting plots, interesting characters, good scripting or challenging puzzles this isn't for you.More detail:There is a consistent plot arc running through the three chapters which is completed without leaving many things unexplained but it lacks any detail.The puzzles are really lacking. Most involve taking undisguised codes from one part of the environment to open a door in another. I found nothing challenging and therefor not satisfying.Any creepy atmosphere the game might have generated was ruined by the horrible navigation mechanism. The same icon is at different times used to move you back a step, make you turn around 180 degrees or  move you back a step followed by turning around 180 degrees. It's disorientating and tedious.  It was annoying enough to stop any spooky atmosphere coming through."
